   {:created-at #inst "2026-04-28T08:00:00.000-00:00",
    :description
    "Read-only introspection ext for SCI sandbox. Lets agent inspect own current turn, conversation history, persisted vars, prior attempts, and provider/code failure diagnostics from `:code`. Plus discover surface + canonical README of every loaded extension. Returns plain Clojure maps/vecs for structural manipulation. `(meta/diagnose)` + `(meta/failures)` = bounded triage. `(meta/extensions)` + `(meta/extension-readme)` = no symbol-name guessing.",
    :content
    "# Meta extension

Pkg: `com.blockether/vis-common-meta`. Src: `extensions/common/vis-common-meta/`.
Canonical: inlined under `[meta :docs \"README.md\"]` in `META-INF/vis-extension/vis.edn`. LLM reads via `(meta/extension-readme 'meta)`.

Opt-in. Lets agent introspect own state, conversation history, failure diagnostics, surface of every loaded ext — all from `:code`. Functions bind under `meta` alias. Return plain maps/vecs.

Pure reads off persistence data. Never throw — errors -> `nil`/`[]`. Use these for triaging stalled turns.

Add jar to classpath, or `com.blockether/vis-common-meta` to `deps.edn`, to enable.

## Current turn snapshot

Call: `(meta/turn)`. One map:

```clojure
{:id          \"uuid\"
 :goal        \"user query text\"
 :status      :running
 :plan        {:goal \"...\" :items [...] :open [...] :decided [...]}
 :breadcrumbs [{:position 0 :breadcrumb \"...\"}]
 :attempts    [{:iteration-id :iteration :code :result :error
                :stdout :stderr :duration-ms}]
 :errors      [...]
 :failures    [{:source :classification :iteration :message :advice}]
 :iteration   {:current N}
 :cost        {:input-tokens :output-tokens :reasoning-tokens
               :cached-tokens :total-cost :model}
 :redundancy  {:duplicate-count N :total-count N :fraction 0.0}
 :elapsed-ms  N}
```

Use for programmatic turn-level manipulation. Plain reads of plan/breadcrumbs/iter pointer = use projection (`<plan>`, `<breadcrumbs>`, `<system_state>`) already in prompt.

## Failure list

Call: `(meta/failures)` or `(meta/failures conversation-id)`. Provider/schema + code/tool failures, normalized:

```clojure
[{:source :provider
  :classification :provider-schema-rejected
  :iteration 4
  :reason :not-a-map
  :received-type \"String\"
  :raw-preview \"Looking at what I have so far\"
  :advice \"...\"}
 {:source :code
  :classification :regex-unsupported-escape
  :tool \"vis/rg\"
  :iteration 9
  :code \"(vis/rg ...)\"
  :message \"Unsupported escape character: \\\\|\"
  :advice \"...\"}]
```

Classifications:

- `:provider-schema-rejected` — provider returned prose/string, not iteration map.
- `:regex-unsupported-escape` — usually `\\|` in Clojure string.
- `:regex-unescaped-quote` — inner quote split a regex string.
- `:patch-unbalanced-string` — malformed `vis/patch` EDN payload.
- `:patch-no-match` — `vis/patch` SEARCH block didn't match exactly.

1-arg form scans every turn in conversation, adds `:turn-id` + `:goal` to each failure.

## Turn diagnosis

Call: `(meta/diagnose)` or `(meta/diagnose conversation-id)`. Compact summary, first stop for stalled-agent triage:

```clojure
{:turn-id \"uuid\"
 :goal \"...\"
 :status :running
 :failure-count 3
 :by-classification {:provider-schema-rejected 1
                     :patch-no-match 2}
 :failures [...]
 :next-actions [\"...\"]}
```

Provider previews, parse/tool error messages, classifications, next actions — all as Clojure data.

## Single conversation snapshot

Call: `(meta/conversation)` or `(meta/conversation conversation-id)`:

```clojure
{:id                \"uuid\"
 :channel           :tui
 :title             \"...\"
 :model             \"claude-sonnet-4-5\"
 :created-at        #inst \"...\"
 :turns             [{:id :goal :outcome :answer :iterations :total-cost}]
 :turn-count        N
 :in-flight-turn-id #uuid \"...\"}  ;; only when current conversation
```

No-arg = current. UUID = any other.

**The in-flight turn is auto-excluded.** When the snapshot covers the
current conversation, the row whose `:id` = `CURRENT_QUERY_ID` is
dropped from `:turns` because its `:iterations` and `:total-cost` are
not finalized yet — listing it would render as `null | $null` in any
markdown table the agent composes. The excluded id is returned as
`:in-flight-turn-id`, so callers who genuinely need to see it can
request the unfiltered snapshot another way (or wait for the turn to
finalize). Foreign conversations (passed `conversation-id` ≠ current)
are returned verbatim — their turns are all complete from this env's
perspective.

## Conversation list

Call: `(meta/conversations)` or `(meta/conversations channel)`. Newest-first vec:

```clojure
[{:id \"...\" :channel :tui :title \"...\" :created-at #inst \"...\"
  :turn-count N :external-id \"...\"}]
```

No-arg scans every registered channel plus `:cli`. Channel kw = filter.

## Var history

Call: `(meta/var-history sym)` or `(meta/var-history sym conversation-id)`. Version timeline:

```clojure
[{:value :code :version 0}
 {:value :code :version 1}]
```

Default = current conversation. UUID = another. `sym` = symbol or string.

## Search past attempts

Call: `(meta/find-attempts pattern)` or `(meta/find-attempts pattern conversation-id)`. Regex over executed `:code`:

```clojure
[{:turn-id :iteration-id :iteration :code :result :error}]
```

1-arg = current turn only. 2-arg = whole conversation. `pattern` = string (compiled to `Pattern`) or `Pattern`.

## Extension catalog

Call: `(meta/extensions)`. Vec of every loaded ext + metadata + summary descriptor per declared doc:

```clojure
[{:namespace 'com.blockether.vis.ext.common-meta.core
  :alias     'meta
  :group     \"meta\"
  :version   \"0.5.0\"
  :doc       \"Meta introspection...\"
  :symbols   [turn conversation conversations var-history
              find-attempts failures diagnose
              extensions extension-docs extension-doc
              extension-readme]
  :docs      [{:name       \"README.md\"
               :created-at #inst \"2026-04-28\"
               :description \"Read-only introspection extension...\"
               :links      [...]
               :reflinks   [...]}]}
 ...]
```

First stop to discover surfaces before reaching for a tool. Summaries omit `:content` to keep catalog small. Pull full descriptor with `(meta/extension-doc ...)` only when needed.

## Extension docs catalog

Call: `(meta/extension-docs)` or `(meta/extension-docs ext-ref)`. No-arg = map keyed by ext id symbol; 1-arg = summary list for one ext. Each entry has all structured fields except `:content`:

```clojure
(meta/extension-docs 'meta)
;; => [{:name       \"README.md\"
;;      :created-at #inst \"2026-04-28\"
;;      :description   \"Read-only introspection extension...\"
;;      :links      [...]   ;; outgoing refs authored in vis.edn
;;      :reflinks   [...]}  ;; inbound refs derived by loader
;;     ...]
```

Index. Scan descriptions + `:links` to pick which full doc is worth pulling.

## Extension doc body

Call: `(meta/extension-doc ext-ref doc-name)`. Full descriptor map for one declared doc, inlined in ext's `META-INF/vis-extension/vis.edn` under `[<id> :docs <doc-name>]`:

```clojure
(meta/extension-doc 'meta \"README.md\")
;; => {:name       \"README.md\"
;;     :created-at #inst \"2026-04-28\"
;;     :description   \"Read-only introspection extension...\"
;;     :content \"# Meta extension\\n...\"   ;; full Markdown body
;;     :links      [...]
;;     :reflinks   [...]}
```

`ext-ref` accepts:

- id symbol (`'meta`),
- id as kw or string (`:meta`, `\"meta\"`),
- alias-ns symbol (`'vis.ext.meta`),
- full ext namespace symbol (`'com.blockether.vis.ext.common-meta.core`).

`nil` when ext not registered or doc-name missing.

## Link types

`:links` = author-declared in `vis.edn`. Four shapes:

- Cross-ext doc: `{:to-id <id> :to-doc <doc-name> :context \"...\"}`
- Same-ext doc (omit `:to-id`): `{:to-doc <doc-name> :context \"...\"}`
- URL: `{:url \"https://...\" :context \"...\"}`
- Repo file: `{:file \"path/to/file.clj\" :context \"...\"}`

`:reflinks` = auto-computed by inverting every cross-ext + same-ext link. URL/file links yield no reflinks. Hand-authored `:reflinks` violate contract — loader overwrites on every merge.

## Extension README

Call: `(meta/extension-readme ext-ref)`. Wrapper for `(meta/extension-doc ext-ref \"README.md\")`. Every ext ships a README, so always works for registered ext.

```clojure
(meta/extension-readme 'meta)
(meta/extension-readme 'com.blockether.vis.ext.common-meta.core)
(meta/extension-readme :vis)             ;; vis-common-editing
(println (meta/extension-readme 'meta))  ;; pretty-print full doc
```

## Use when

- Failure triage without leaving sandbox: `(meta/diagnose)` / `(meta/failures)`.
- Verify what an ext does: `(meta/extension-readme 'some-ext)` — no guessing from symbol names.
- Programmatic state manipulation: `(filter :error (:attempts (meta/turn)))`.
- Inspect a different conversation than current.
- Regex search over historical attempts.
- Token / cost visibility.

## Don't use when

- State already in projection (`<plan>` `<breadcrumbs>` `<system_state>` `<var_index>`). Projection = free; `meta/*` costs an iter round-trip.
- As substitute for `:doc` on code blocks. Use the spec field for purpose, not introspection.

## Implementation notes

- **Environment-aware via `:before-fn` injection.** Each impl fn takes env map as 1st param. Shared `inject-environment` hook prepends env to args vec, so model still calls `(meta/turn)` with 0 args.
- **No side effects, never throws.** Pure reads. Misconfigured context -> `nil`/`[]`. Iteration unaffected.
- **No schema change.** Reads existing conversation/query/iteration/expression rows via persistence facade.
- **README discovery.** Every ext declares canonical README inline in `META-INF/vis-extension/vis.edn` under `[<id> :docs \"README.md\"]` (see `AGENTS.md` ▸ \"Every extension declares itself in vis.edn with an inline README\"). Each doc descriptor MUST carry `:description` (one-paragraph summary) + `:content` (full Markdown body) as plain EDN strings — NOT YAML frontmatter parsed from Markdown. `(meta/extensions)`, `(meta/extension-docs ...)`, `(meta/extension-doc ...)`, `(meta/extension-readme ...)` all read from this structured registry.
